==Arabic==
===Etymology===
From the verb {{ARchar|[[حمد]]}} (ħámida), meaning to praise, commend, laud.

===Alternative spellings===
*{{ARchar|[[ﷴ]]}}

===Proper names===
'''{{ARchar|محمّدٌ}}''' (muħámmad) {{m}}

# a male [[given name]], variously transliterated as: [[Muhammad]], [[Mohammed]], [[Mohamed]], [[Muhamed]], [[Mohamet]], etc.
# the prophet [[Muhammad]].

===Adjective===
'''{{ARchar|محمّد}}''' (muħámmad)

# [[praise]]d, [[commendable]], [[laudable]].

